ACCEL_AUX_RPT

ID Decimal 768
ID Hexadecimal 0x300
Frame Format Standard
DLC 6
Sender PACMOD
Send Type Cyclic
Interval (ms) 33

Supported Vehicles:

Ford Ranger, Freightliner, Lexus RX 450h, Ford Transit, Development Vehicle 01, MKZ, Polaris Ranger, Development Vehicle 02, Development Vehicle 03, Development Vehicle 04

Name Type Bitpos Length Factor Offset Min Max Unit
OPERATOR_INTERACTION 1 a Unsigned 32 1 1 0 0 1
ACCEL_LIMITING_ACTIVE 2 b Unsigned 33 1 1 0 0 1
PRK_BRK_INTERLOCK_ACTIVE 2 c Unsigned 34 1 1 0 0 1
BRAKE_INTERLOCK_ACTIVE 2 d Unsigned 35 1 1 0 0 1
CALIBRATION_STATUS 3 e Unsigned 38 3 1 0 0 3
OPERATOR_INTERACTION_AVAIL 4 f Unsigned 42 1 1 0 0 1
ACCEL_LIMITING_ACTIVE_AVAIL 4 f Unsigned 43 1 1 0 0 1
PRK_BRK_INTERLOCK_ACTIVE_AVAIL 4 f Unsigned 44 1 1 0 0 1
BRAKE_INTERLOCK_ACTIVE_AVAIL 4 f Unsigned 45 1 1 0 0 1

1 0=NO_INTERACTION, 1=INTERACTION

2 0=NOT_ACTIVE, 1=ACTIVE

3 0=INACTIVE, 1=ACTIVE, 2=COMPLETE, 3=ERROR

4 0=NOT_AVAILABLE, 1=AVAILABLE

a OPERATOR_INTERACTION shall have the value of 1 if the driver is moving, changing, or otherwise touching the operator control(s) that relates to this signal to an extent that is detectable. Otherwise, the value shall be 0.

b ACCEL_LIMITING_ACTIVE shall have the value of 1 if a limiting function is reducing an excessive command. Otherwise, the value shall be 0.

c PARK_BRAKE_INTERLOCK_ACTIVE shall have the value of 1 if an active parking brake prevents or reduces the command. Otherwise, the value shall be 0.

d BRAKE_INTERLOCK_ACTIVE shall have the value of 1 if an active brake prevents or reduces the command. Otherwise, the value shall be 0.

e CALIBRATION_STATUS shall indicate the status of a calibration of this system. If this system has more than one calibration, then those calibrations are INACTIVE.

f PACMod sets this value as a function of which vehicle platform is under test and, therefore, this value does not change during operation.

5 0=NOT_ACTIVE, 1=ACTIVE

6 0=INACTIVE, 1=ACTIVE, 2=COMPLETE, 3=ERROR

7 0=LOW_SPEED, 1=HIGH_SPEED

8 0=NOT_AVAILABLE, 1=AVAILABLE

a Ratio of full-scale value of signal from -1 to 1 (i.e. percent from -1 to 1) possibly exceeding -1 and 1.

b OPERATOR_INTERACTION shall have the value of 1 if the driver is moving, changing, or otherwise touching the operator control(s) that relates to this signal to an extent that is detectable. Otherwise, the value shall be 0.

c Counterclockwise rotation is positive according to the right-hand rule.

d STEERING_LIMITING_ACTIVE shall have the value of 1 if a limiting function is reducing an excessive command. Otherwise, the value shall be 0.

e CALIBRATION_STATUS shall indicate the status of a calibration of this system. If this system has more than one calibration, then those calibrations are INACTIVE.

f STEERING_CONTROLER_TYPE indicates which steering controller is the PACMod System is using.

g PACMod sets this value as a function of which vehicle platform is under test and, therefore, this value does not change during operation.

USER_PC_HEALTH_RPT_00

ID Decimal 37
ID Hexadecimal 0x25
Frame Format Standard
DLC 3
Sender CUSTOMER_ECU
Send Type Cyclic
Interval (ms) 33

Supported Vehicles:

Development Vehicle 03, Development Vehicle 04

Name Type Bitpos Length Factor Offset Min Max Unit
COUNTER a Unsigned 7 8 1 0 0 255
CHECKSUM b Unsigned 15 8 1 0 0 255
USER_PC_APPLICATION_FAULT 1 c Unsigned 16 1 1 0 0 1

1 0=NO_FAULT, 1=FAULT

a The COUNTER shall have the value of 0 with the first message transmission. It shall increase by 1 with each subsequent message transmission up to and including the value of 0xFF. The next message transmission shall be 0, and this pattern shall repeat.

b The CHECKSUM shall be the least significant byte of the sum of the message ID and the COUNTER. For example, if COUNTER is 0xFB and the message ID is 0x25, then the sum is 0x0120 and the checksum is 0x20.

c This signal allows the User PC application to report a fault in its operation.
